    {
      "name": "Components of the .NET Framework",
      "slug": "components-of-the-dotnet-framework",
      "level": "Draft",
      "focus": "Preview",
      "summary": ".NET Framework consists of three components. Execution environment is called the Common Language Runtime (CLR). The CLR manages program execution at run time. The Base Class Library (BCL) is a large class library used by the .NET Framework and available for you to use in your programs as well.",
      "dotnetZone": "foundation",
      "dotnetZoneStep": "csharp-dotnet",
      "order": 1,
      "tags": [
        ".NET Framework"
      ],
